          <msItem n="1" xml:id="a1" defective="true">
                <locus from="1" to="49"/>
            <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/13" type="supplied">The first book of Chronicles, according to the Peshitta version.</title>
                <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܣܦܪ ܕܘܒܪ ܝܘܡ̈ܬܐ ܕܡ̈ܠܟܐ ܕܝܗܘܕܐ ܕܡܬܩܪܐ ܣܦܪ  ܕܒܪܝܡܝܢ.<locus from="1b" to="1b"/></rubric>
      <!-- ARABIC NEEDED ^^^-->
                <note>The missing portions are : ch. xiv. 12—xvii. 27, and xxii. 8 to the end.</note>
              </msItem>
              <msItem n="2" xml:id="a2" defective="true">
                <locus from="49b" to="104b"/>
                <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/14" type="supplied">The second book of Chronicles, according to the Peshitta version.</title>
                <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܦܠܓܘܬܐ ܐܚܪܝܬܐ ܕܣܦܪ ܕܒܪܝܡܝܢ<locus from="49b" to="49b"/></rubric>
                <note>It commences with ch. vi. 1 of the Hebrew text. The missing portions are: ch. xviii. 19—29, xx. 24—32, and ch. xxix. 5 to the end.</note>
               </msItem>
            </msContents>
            <physDesc>
              <objectDesc form="codex">
                <supportDesc material="perg">
                  <support>
                    <material>Vellum</material>
                  </support>
                  <extent>
                    <measure type="composition" unit="leaf" quantity="104">104 ff.</measure>
                    <dimensions type="leaf" unit="in">
                      <height>
                        <measure type="height" quantity="8.5" unit="in">8 1/2</measure>
                      </height>
                      <width>
                        <measure type="width" quantity="5.375" unit="in">5 3/8</measure>
                      </width>
                    </dimensions>
                  </extent>
                  <foliation type="ancient"/>
                  <collation>
                    <p>The quires are at present 11 in number, but ܗ, ܙ, ܚ, and ܛ have been lost, as well as several at the end. What the original signatures of the quires were, does not appear; they are now signed with letters.</p>
                  </collation>
                  <condition>
                    <p>Some of the leaves are much stained and torn, especially <locus>fol. 1, 2, 8, 28, 39, 47, 48, 55, 77, 78, 103 and 104</locus>. Leaves are also missing after <locus>foll. 79 and 84</locus></p>
                  </condition>
                </supportDesc>
                <layoutDesc>
                  <layout columns="1" writtenLines="18 21">
                    <p>There are from 18 to 21 lines in each page.</p>
                  </layout>
                </layoutDesc>
              </objectDesc>
              <handDesc>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr-Syre" medium="unknown">
                  <desc>The writing is a small, regular Estrangela of the <origDate notBefore="0500" notAfter="0600">vith cent.</origDate> </desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handnote2" scope="minor" script="syr-Syrj" medium="uknown">
                  <desc>Numerous Greek vowels have been added by a later hand (α, ε, ⲏ, ω, ὄ and αυ; e.g. ܘܢܺܬܢܺܐܝܶܠ, ܘܐܘܨܡ, ܘܝܘܐܒ, ܝܬ, ܠܡ̇ܢܘ). The same hand that added the vowel-points has divided the books into sections, marked by Greek letters on the margins. The last of these in 1 Chronicles is ϊθ (ch. xxii. 2), <locus>fol. 48 a</locus>; and in 2 Chronicles (commencing with Δ) ΚΓ (ch. xxix. 1), <locus>fol. 104 b</locus>.</desc>
                </handNote>
   <!-- Missing other vowels on top of these syriac words!!! -->
              </handDesc>
              <additions>
                <p>There are also a few marginal notes and glosses</p>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1"><locus from="3a" to="3a"/><ref target="#a1"/>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܘܐܺܘܝܡ,</quote><label>marg.</label><quote xml:lang="grc">ηαμ</quote></item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="addition2"><locus from="11b" to="11b"/><ref target="#a1"/>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܣܩܐ̣</quote>,<label>marg.</label><quote xml:lang="grc">ⲤⲔⲰ</quote></item>
    <!-- GREEK not showing ^^^ -->
